contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

22:58.000 --> 23:00.868
[SHOWER RUNNING, CALLIE GIGGLES]

23:00.868 --> 23:03.767
CALLIE:
You know, you wouldn't have
believed this party last night.

23:03.767 --> 23:06.033
I mean, it was pretty normal,
you know,

23:06.033 --> 23:09.934
and then for some weird reason,
Chris Isaak shows up.

23:09.934 --> 23:11.434
You know, the singer?

23:11.434 --> 23:13.267
And someone had a guitar.

23:13.267 --> 23:14.734
So Chris Isaak borrows it,

23:14.734 --> 23:17.567
and he starts
singing camp songs, you know?

23:17.567 --> 23:21.968
Like, um-- Like-- Like"John
Jacob Jingleheimer Schmidt."

23:21.968 --> 23:25.067
And then-- And then someone dug
up chocolate and marshmallows.

23:25.067 --> 23:27.334
So at 3 a.m., okay?

23:27.334 --> 23:30.133
We're sitting in the kitchen
making s'mores,

23:30.133 --> 23:34.067
singing "B-I-N-G-O"
with Chris Isaak.

23:34.067 --> 23:35.400
It was so fun.

23:35.400 --> 23:37.200
You totally should have come.

23:38.400 --> 23:39.801
What were you doing, anyway?

23:39.801 --> 23:41.033
Working?

23:41.767 --> 23:43.934
[BAILEY SIGHS]

23:45.167 --> 23:47.467
How do your parents
take their coffee?

23:47.467 --> 23:50.067
With milk,
both of them, why?

23:50.067 --> 23:51.567
What the hell
are they doing here?

23:53.067 --> 23:55.400
They called to see if we needed
any help with the party.

23:55.400 --> 23:58.067
We don't. You said last night we
have everything under control.

23:58.067 --> 24:00.367
I know. But they're
just trying to be nice, so--

24:00.367 --> 24:02.367
No, they're not.
They're casing the joint.

24:02.367 --> 24:03.968
[LAUGHS]
Look, just you watch.

24:03.968 --> 24:05.868
In a week, my mother will send
fabric swatches

24:05.868 --> 24:07.968
offering to make new curtains
for the living room.

24:07.968 --> 24:09.968
No, thanks.
No, hang on. What are you doing?

24:09.968 --> 24:11.133
I'm telling them
to leave.

24:11.133 --> 24:14.033
Whoa! No, look, I--

24:14.033 --> 24:16.534
I shouldn't have said they could
stop by without asking you.

24:16.534 --> 24:17.968
But you can't
kick them out.

24:17.968 --> 24:19.767
I kick them
out of my place all the time.

24:19.767 --> 24:21.367
It's the only way
to get them to leave.

24:21.367 --> 24:23.067
No, uh-uh, look, I--
I like them, so--

24:23.067 --> 24:25.133
You don't even know them. And
they don't know you.

24:25.133 --> 24:26.734
This whole
liking each other thing-- 

24:26.734 --> 24:29.033
You do know you're
sounding insane, right?

24:29.033 --> 24:31.400
Forget it. Bring them coffee.

24:31.400 --> 24:33.601
Throw in a cookie or two.
Kiss their butts, whatever.

24:36.534 --> 24:40.934
[CHATTERING, SHOUTING,
CHILDREN'S MUSIC PLAYING]

24:40.934 --> 24:42.367
Oh, careful there.

24:45.400 --> 24:47.133
Boo-- Oh.

24:47.133 --> 24:49.200
[HUMMING]
[LAUGHS]

24:49.200 --> 24:51.801
JULIA:
Okay, well, if he gets home
tell him that he and a clown

24:51.801 --> 24:54.000
were due here an hour ago.

24:54.000 --> 24:55.767
[PHONE BEEPS OFF]
He'll be here.

24:55.767 --> 24:58.167
I had a long talk
with him yesterday.

24:58.167 --> 24:59.501
It'll be fine.

25:00.767 --> 25:03.434
[DOORBELL RINGS]
Finally.

25:07.801 --> 25:10.067
Oh, you're not a clown.

25:10.067 --> 25:11.701
Glad you think so.

25:11.701 --> 25:13.801
But I--?
I thought you had to work?

25:13.801 --> 25:15.334
Remodel, shmemodel.

25:15.334 --> 25:16.934
They're gonna beep me
if they need me.

25:16.934 --> 25:18.400
Give me a kiss.

25:21.634 --> 25:23.868
Twist, twist, twist.

25:23.868 --> 25:24.868
[BLOWS]

25:24.868 --> 25:25.934
It's gone.

25:25.934 --> 25:27.868
[CHILDREN CHEERING]

25:30.200 --> 25:33.968
He used to do that for our girls
when they were little.

25:33.968 --> 25:36.634
I bet Grace was adorable
as a kid.

25:36.634 --> 25:40.100
Oh, you said
the magic words.

25:40.100 --> 25:42.634
Really? Bring 'em on. Heh-heh!
[CHUCKLES]

25:44.067 --> 25:46.167
Oh. Oh, she was
about 5 years old there.

25:46.167 --> 25:48.167
Beautiful.
Yeah.

25:48.167 --> 25:49.767
You know what?

25:49.767 --> 25:52.934
Every summer Martin
and I take a place in Carmel.

25:52.934 --> 25:55.801
You and Grace should come up
and visit us for a week.

25:55.801 --> 25:57.300
That sounds like fun, Rose.

25:57.300 --> 25:58.467
We'll see if we can swing it.

25:58.467 --> 26:00.400
Good. Heh-heh!

26:02.868 --> 26:05.534
Um, Rose, I'll--
I'll be back in one second.

26:05.534 --> 26:06.834
Okay?

26:11.734 --> 26:12.934
Okay.

26:12.934 --> 26:14.968
What'd I do wrong?

26:14.968 --> 26:17.434
Am I being too nice?

26:17.434 --> 26:20.000
Is that it? You think
I'm kissing up to them?

26:20.000 --> 26:23.601
No, you're not.
That's the problem.

26:23.601 --> 26:25.667
You're just being you.

26:25.667 --> 26:26.934
Right.

26:26.934 --> 26:28.234
Okay, that's the problem.

26:28.234 --> 26:30.300
I'll just start
being someone else.

26:31.534 --> 26:33.400
No, wait. Look, it's...

26:34.200 --> 26:35.834
[SIGHS]

26:35.834 --> 26:40.200
In my whole life I've been
struggling to find a me

26:40.200 --> 26:42.000
that's different than them.

26:42.000 --> 26:44.200
Honestly, it's like...

26:44.200 --> 26:47.901
My meter for making decisions:
If they object, do it.

26:47.901 --> 26:50.033
Then all of a sudden,
I fall in love with you.

26:50.033 --> 26:51.534
And outta nowhere,
they decide

26:51.534 --> 26:53.567
it's the best idea
they've ever heard.

26:55.100 --> 26:56.667
So?

26:56.667 --> 26:58.868
So they're out there right now
thinking they've won.

26:58.868 --> 27:02.767
Thinking I've stepped in line
and I've decided to behave

27:02.767 --> 27:04.334
or something. It's just...

27:04.834 --> 27:07.300
[SIGHS]

27:07.300 --> 27:09.234
Look, I know that's
not what's going on here,

27:09.234 --> 27:10.734
and you know it.

27:10.734 --> 27:13.000
What's the harm in letting them
think that they've won

27:13.000 --> 27:15.567
just this once?
Well, the harm is...

27:15.567 --> 27:18.033
The harm is...

27:18.033 --> 27:19.834
The harm is it bugs me.

27:19.834 --> 27:21.534
Look, I know I'm being
a baby about this.

27:21.534 --> 27:25.067
But can't you just let me
do that just this once?

27:29.000 --> 27:30.767
Just this once.

27:34.400 --> 27:36.801
Cake time.

27:36.801 --> 27:38.100
Cake time.

27:43.567 --> 27:45.567
[SLURRING]
Hey, I'm in here.

27:45.567 --> 27:47.000
Bailey, what are you--?

27:47.000 --> 27:48.467
I thought you were
hiring a clown.

27:48.467 --> 27:50.467
Clowns are expensive.

27:50.467 --> 27:52.901
And very hard to book
at the last minute.

27:52.901 --> 27:55.501
"Nope, I can't do it."

27:55.501 --> 27:58.067
"Sorry, I'm busy." Jerks.

27:58.067 --> 28:00.033
Are you okay? Maybe you should--

28:00.033 --> 28:02.133
You know what, Grace?

28:02.133 --> 28:05.234
You tell too many people
what to do.

28:05.234 --> 28:07.734
Maybe if you were
less of a bitch,

28:07.734 --> 28:09.534
more people would like you.

28:12.400 --> 28:13.701
There. You see?

28:13.701 --> 28:15.634
You can't even see it.

28:16.567 --> 28:18.067
SAM:
Right.

28:18.067 --> 28:20.501
That's one punch and one soda.

28:20.501 --> 28:21.734
Thank you.
You're welcome.

28:21.734 --> 28:23.801
[PAGER BEEPS]
Whoops.

28:23.801 --> 28:25.367
Oh, that's the site.

28:25.367 --> 28:27.834
I'd love to stay and talk,
but I gotta get back to work.

28:27.834 --> 28:28.901
ROSE:
Oh, that's okay.

28:28.901 --> 28:30.133
You have
your own business.

28:30.133 --> 28:32.501
Right, which means instead
of working a 40-hour week

28:32.501 --> 28:34.801
for someone else, I work
a 100-hour week for myself.

28:34.801 --> 28:36.133
[MARTIN CHUCKLES]

28:36.133 --> 28:37.934
SAM:
It's crazy, huh?

28:37.934 --> 28:39.467
Well, it was nice
meeting you both.

28:39.467 --> 28:41.667
You too.
Bye-bye.

28:46.901 --> 28:49.634
We should have Grace's mom take
a picture of all five of us,

28:49.634 --> 28:52.033
since... Well, we haven't had
our picture taken together

28:52.033 --> 28:53.901
in a while, so...

28:55.367 --> 28:57.300
Hee! Bailey.
Hey, what the hell--?

28:57.300 --> 28:59.267
Every clown was booked.
[LAUGHS]

28:59.267 --> 29:00.968
This whole thing's
been a major hassle,

29:00.968 --> 29:03.067
and I don't need to hear about
it from either of you.

29:03.067 --> 29:05.501
Sorry.
Give me this.

29:05.501 --> 29:07.000
[SHOES SQUEAKING]

29:07.000 --> 29:08.534
[CLAUDIA LAUGHS]

29:12.601 --> 29:15.100
So you feeling better?

29:15.100 --> 29:16.634
About what?

29:16.634 --> 29:18.634
Oh, man, you didn't see?

29:18.634 --> 29:19.968
I was a saint
to those people.

29:19.968 --> 29:22.334
I brought 'em drinks,
chatted with 'em.

29:22.334 --> 29:23.534
[SIGHS]

29:25.534 --> 29:27.901
I'll try and swing by
after work, okay?

29:27.901 --> 29:31.534
CROWD:
* Happy birthday to you *

29:31.534 --> 29:34.734
* Happy birthday to you *

29:34.734 --> 29:38.300
* Happy birthday, dear Owen *

29:38.300 --> 29:42.801
* Happy birthday to you *

29:42.801 --> 29:44.100
[ALL CHEERING]

29:44.100 --> 29:45.534
Well, that pretty much sucked.

29:45.534 --> 29:46.901
[BLOWING]

29:46.901 --> 29:48.167
WOMAN:
Blow it out...

29:48.167 --> 29:50.200
Yeah!
[CHEERING]

29:50.200 --> 29:51.734
Whoa!

29:51.734 --> 29:53.534
Bailey.

29:53.534 --> 29:55.834
Who the hell put that there?

29:55.834 --> 29:57.934
What's going on?
CHARLIE: He's ripped.

29:57.934 --> 29:59.400
Oh, my God.
He--? He's what?

29:59.400 --> 30:01.901
Drunk. Really drunk.

30:01.901 --> 30:03.501
Okay, so it's a little
messed up,

30:03.501 --> 30:05.501
but it's more fun
that way, right?

30:05.501 --> 30:06.968
Hey, what did you expect?!

30:06.968 --> 30:08.367
I never done this before.

30:08.367 --> 30:11.100
You expect a first-time clown
not to make any mistakes?

30:11.100 --> 30:12.367
Huh?!

30:12.367 --> 30:13.534
[SOBBING]
I want my mom.

30:13.534 --> 30:15.734
Oh, God, don't cry.
He's crying!

30:15.734 --> 30:17.334
Bay, come on,
let's get outta here.

30:17.334 --> 30:18.901
I'm talking to my friend, here.

30:18.901 --> 30:20.300
I'm teaching him
how to be a man.

30:20.300 --> 30:21.601
CHARLIE:
Bay, I said, come on.

30:21.601 --> 30:24.100
BAILEY:
I said, I'm talking!

30:24.100 --> 30:26.267
Charlie.
Oh, my God.

30:26.267 --> 30:27.601
[***]

30:27.601 --> 30:29.767
Charlie, are you okay?

30:29.767 --> 30:30.968
I'm fine.

30:36.968 --> 30:39.334
It was-- He pushed...

30:40.200 --> 30:42.100
It was an accident.

30:45.367 --> 30:47.934
The hell with all you.

30:49.300 --> 30:51.234
WOMAN:
I think it's time to go.

30:51.234 --> 30:53.033
MAN:
I think that's a good idea.

30:59.400 --> 31:01.501
Bay?

31:01.501 --> 31:02.968
Are--? Are you gonna be okay?

31:02.968 --> 31:04.801
Get out.

31:04.801 --> 31:06.400
Come on, Bay, please.

31:06.400 --> 31:08.734
Please don't be like this.

31:10.567 --> 31:12.467
Y-you're just up-- Upset
or something.

31:12.467 --> 31:14.267
I'm not upset.

31:14.267 --> 31:17.234
I just don't wanna hear
your stupid whiny voice!

31:17.234 --> 31:18.467
Now get the hell out!

31:18.467 --> 31:20.467
[INHALES SHARPLY]

31:20.467 --> 31:22.400
[***]

31:37.667 --> 31:39.334
I put him in Owen's room.

31:40.534 --> 31:41.834
He's out.

31:44.334 --> 31:46.701
They'll be talking about
this one at the sandbox, huh?

31:52.467 --> 31:54.868
[***]

31:58.567 --> 32:00.234
Oh, man.

32:05.634 --> 32:07.300
Wake up, Bailey.

32:08.834 --> 32:10.834
Look at my new hat.

32:14.100 --> 32:15.400
Wake up.

32:17.200 --> 32:18.734
Wake up.

32:24.567 --> 32:27.901
Well, I'm really sorry
about all this.

32:27.901 --> 32:30.701
You've got nothing
to apologize for, Charlie.

32:39.000 --> 32:40.801
You know, Charlie,

32:40.801 --> 32:42.801
my sister-in-law
had this problem.

32:42.801 --> 32:45.868
I did a lot of research
into treatment.

32:45.868 --> 32:48.100
Treatment?

32:48.100 --> 32:49.501
For alcoholism.

32:50.767 --> 32:52.968
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

32:52.968 --> 32:55.434
Look, Bay's-- He's not a--

32:55.434 --> 32:58.501
He's just a...
He's a kid in college.

32:58.501 --> 33:00.534
I don't think so, Charlie.

33:02.634 --> 33:05.434
Okay. Look, you've just met him.

33:05.434 --> 33:07.968
I've known him
his whole life, so...

33:09.467 --> 33:11.801
Um...

33:11.801 --> 33:14.234
Well, drive carefully.

33:29.801 --> 33:31.300
Sarah.

33:31.300 --> 33:34.200
Oh, Julia,
I didn't see you.

33:36.033 --> 33:37.667
Here, this is for Owen.

33:37.667 --> 33:40.000
I figured if I came by late
that, you know,

33:40.000 --> 33:41.501
the odds of my running
into Bailey

33:41.501 --> 33:43.934
were significantly diminished,
so...

33:43.934 --> 33:46.067
Hey, are you crying?

33:47.534 --> 33:49.767
Yeah.

33:49.767 --> 33:51.934
What--? What happened?

33:53.267 --> 33:55.100
Everything...

33:55.100 --> 33:58.367
is just so screwed up.

33:58.367 --> 34:02.400
Okay, can--? Can you be, like,
a little more specific?

34:02.400 --> 34:04.567
Bailey.

34:04.567 --> 34:08.199
He ruined Owen's party.

34:08.199 --> 34:11.400
It was just awful.

34:11.400 --> 34:13.132
My God.

34:13.132 --> 34:14.367
Was he drunk?

34:18.199 --> 34:19.634
You know,

34:19.634 --> 34:24.067
for five minutes yesterday
he was himself.

34:24.067 --> 34:27.667
And then he drinks,
and he just turns into this...

34:27.667 --> 34:29.266
[***]

34:29.266 --> 34:31.601
God, Sarah.

34:33.000 --> 34:34.967
It's really bad,
isn't it?

34:39.234 --> 34:40.801
Is he still here?

34:42.199 --> 34:43.967
Yeah, he's passed out.

34:49.801 --> 34:51.667
He was right--
He must have woken up.

34:51.667 --> 34:53.701
Charlie!

34:55.400 --> 34:56.400
Damn it.

34:56.400 --> 34:57.567
What?

34:57.567 --> 34:59.000
His jeep is gone.

34:59.000 --> 35:00.067
He's gone.

35:01.200 --> 35:02.968
[SIGHS]

35:05.734 --> 35:07.801
Hi, Marcus.

35:07.801 --> 35:09.400
Mark.

35:11.300 --> 35:13.234
I was just--
He's not here.

35:14.601 --> 35:15.734
Oh.

35:17.400 --> 35:18.934
Well, is he gonna
be back soon?

35:18.934 --> 35:21.701
He's just out, okay?

35:21.701 --> 35:24.901
Do you have to know
his whole schedule?

35:24.901 --> 35:26.033
I'll...

35:26.033 --> 35:28.701
I'll come back later.
Oh, great.

35:28.701 --> 35:30.701
Why don't you come back
when it's just him and me

35:30.701 --> 35:32.767
so he'll have someone
interesting to talk to?

35:35.200 --> 35:37.968
I didn't mean to...

35:37.968 --> 35:39.868
intrude.
Wow.

35:39.868 --> 35:42.534
You do it without even trying.

35:42.534 --> 35:44.133
You must be one
of those gifted kids.

35:44.133 --> 35:46.033
No wonder he likes you so much.

35:47.968 --> 35:49.901
[CRYING]

35:54.567 --> 35:56.033
Oh, God.

35:56.033 --> 35:56.968
Don't.

36:00.067 --> 36:01.367
L-look...

36:01.367 --> 36:02.634
[SIGHS]

36:02.634 --> 36:03.901
...I'm sorry.

36:03.901 --> 36:06.400
I'm not crying about you,
you stupid idiot.

36:06.400 --> 36:09.100
I couldn't care less about you.

36:09.100 --> 36:11.868
It's just my whole
family, it's--

36:11.868 --> 36:13.834
They're falling apart,

36:13.834 --> 36:16.834
and I-- I don't know what...

36:18.801 --> 36:19.934
[INHALES SHARPLY]

36:19.934 --> 36:22.300
What am I supposed to do?

36:24.834 --> 36:28.434
There's a <i>Tricky Rock Block</i>
playing.

36:29.667 --> 36:31.801
Do you wanna come in
and watch?

36:53.234 --> 36:55.434
Hey, is, uh, Julia around?

36:55.434 --> 36:57.367
Yeah, she's out back.

37:06.300 --> 37:07.801
Hi.

37:13.567 --> 37:15.567
What's the matter?

37:15.567 --> 37:16.601
Did I do something?

37:17.868 --> 37:21.267
Yeah, you-- You did.

37:21.267 --> 37:23.634
And I know that you probably
think that you-- You didn't.

37:23.634 --> 37:27.567
I know you-- It was probably
just another joke or something.

37:27.567 --> 37:29.567
Oh, man, not this again.

37:29.567 --> 37:32.801
God, Julia, there is nothing
wrong with joking a little.

37:32.801 --> 37:35.334
I-I know you think that.

37:35.334 --> 37:39.534
And I-I can't convince you
that-- That how you are

37:39.534 --> 37:42.300
or-- Or how you think, that--
That it's bad.

37:42.300 --> 37:44.567
It's just...

37:44.567 --> 37:46.400
for me, I know it is.

37:48.400 --> 37:49.601
And...

37:51.434 --> 37:55.534
I don't know how to be with
someone who thinks that way.

37:55.534 --> 37:57.033
So...

37:58.701 --> 38:00.234
Hey, wait. Jule--

38:00.234 --> 38:02.801
No, I-I feel sick, Sam.

38:02.801 --> 38:05.367
When I let the things that you
said run around in my head,

38:05.367 --> 38:07.033
I feel ill.

38:08.767 --> 38:10.467
S-so...

38:11.300 --> 38:13.033
what?

38:13.033 --> 38:14.501
Are you ending this?

38:14.501 --> 38:18.267
'Cause that-- That--
That's insane.

38:18.267 --> 38:20.968
Julia, to just casually
end a relationship--

38:20.968 --> 38:23.000
You think this is casual?

38:25.033 --> 38:28.934
You did so much for me, Sam.

38:28.934 --> 38:31.133
You, like, walked into my life,

38:31.133 --> 38:34.100
and you-- You turned it into
something better, and that's--

38:34.100 --> 38:37.868
That is an amazing thing
to do for someone.

38:40.100 --> 38:42.367
And then,

38:42.367 --> 38:45.267
just by being this way,

38:45.267 --> 38:47.934
how you are,

38:47.934 --> 38:50.767
who you are,
y-you took that away.

38:55.501 --> 38:58.100
I think you should go.

39:00.567 --> 39:02.868
This is...

39:02.868 --> 39:05.701
This is not us here.

39:05.701 --> 39:10.367
This is an argument about
a stupid moral or ethical--

39:10.367 --> 39:12.667
I-I don't know, a political
thing. It is nothing.

39:12.667 --> 39:14.300
I just told you
that I care about this.

39:14.300 --> 39:15.868
Don't call it nothing.

39:15.868 --> 39:17.934
Julia--
I-I really--

39:17.934 --> 39:19.934
I really think you should go.

39:21.100 --> 39:23.033
[***]

39:45.234 --> 39:46.734
Sam left?

39:46.734 --> 39:47.734
Yeah.

39:47.734 --> 39:49.300
I told him to.

39:50.334 --> 39:51.801
Why?

39:52.801 --> 39:54.467
You mean because of...?

39:57.300 --> 40:00.734
So is it--?
Is that it?

40:04.400 --> 40:06.767
I'm sorry.

40:06.767 --> 40:08.701
[***]

40:13.434 --> 40:16.868
You know, if there's-- There's
something so awful in someone,

40:16.868 --> 40:20.467
something you know
you can't live with,

40:20.467 --> 40:23.734
it should erase
all the good things.

40:25.467 --> 40:27.667
Yeah, I know.

40:27.667 --> 40:30.234
It should make it easy
to walk away.

40:33.767 --> 40:35.701
[DISHES CLINKING]

40:38.767 --> 40:40.834
You and I are gonna write notes
to all your friends

40:40.834 --> 40:43.234
and thank them for the presents,
'cause that's what you do

40:43.234 --> 40:46.267
when someone does
something nice for you.

40:46.267 --> 40:48.033
Thank you.
Just like that.

40:48.033 --> 40:49.968
[IMITATING MOTOR]

40:52.300 --> 40:53.767
When did you get back?

40:53.767 --> 40:55.334
Just.

40:55.334 --> 40:56.868
I dropped them off
at the station.

40:56.868 --> 40:58.234
Mom took more pictures.

40:58.234 --> 41:00.601
Dad cried.
The whole routine.

41:00.601 --> 41:04.634
I see what you were saying
now about them.

41:04.634 --> 41:07.167
About how they stick their noses
in when they don't belong.

41:07.167 --> 41:08.300
[SCOFFS]

41:09.267 --> 41:10.801
Man, your dad.

41:10.801 --> 41:13.834
Who did he think he was
going on about Bailey like that?

41:13.834 --> 41:15.901
Yeah. None of his business.

41:18.567 --> 41:20.868
But, um...

41:20.868 --> 41:24.367
for the record, I'm sorry,
but I think he's right.

41:24.367 --> 41:26.434
[SCOFFS]

41:26.434 --> 41:27.567
Are you kidding me?

41:32.767 --> 41:36.767
Grace, he-- He's in college.
He's a freshman.

41:36.767 --> 41:40.133
He's got, like, crappy judgment
and all that,

41:40.133 --> 41:41.467
but he's not a...

41:43.868 --> 41:46.334
He's exactly like I was then.

41:46.334 --> 41:49.534
Did you ever hit anyone in your
family? 'Cause he hit you.

41:49.534 --> 41:51.934
Look, all I know is that I've
been out of control like that.

41:51.934 --> 41:53.200
I was like that.

41:53.200 --> 41:56.434
He's just--
He's just doing what I did.

41:56.434 --> 41:57.801
JULIA:
No.

41:57.801 --> 41:59.734
Charlie, he's different.

42:01.934 --> 42:04.801
You drank, a lot,

42:04.801 --> 42:07.067
but you were always you.

42:17.434 --> 42:19.667
[SIGHS]
[PHONE RINGS]

42:21.000 --> 42:22.033
[PHONE BEEPS]

42:22.033 --> 42:23.000
Bailey?

42:24.934 --> 42:26.100
Okay.

42:27.334 --> 42:29.400
Thanks for calling back.

42:29.400 --> 42:31.000
[PHONE BEEPS OFF]

42:31.000 --> 42:33.767
It was Callie.
She hasn't seen him.

42:33.767 --> 42:36.534
And his car's
not there either.

42:36.534 --> 42:38.968
But, uh, she's gonna
have him call us

42:38.968 --> 42:40.767
as soon as he gets in.

42:40.767 --> 42:42.334
[***]

42:54.100 --> 42:55.567
He'll call.

